Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the CheckWise frontend.

## What Was Done

### 1. Fetched Latest Documentation
- Retrieved the latest installation instructions from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart
- Confirmed the project uses Next.js App Router architecture

### 2. Installed Package
- Added `@vercel/analytics` package to dependencies using npm
- Package version installed: latest available from npm registry

### 3. Configured Analytics Component
- Added Analytics component to the root layout file following official Next.js App Router instructions
- Location: `frontend/app/layout.tsx`

## Changes Made

### Modified Files:
- **frontend/app/layout.tsx**
  - Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
  - Added `<Analytics />` component at the end of the body element, after the existing `<Toaster />` component
  - Preserved all existing code structure and components

- **frontend/package.json**
  - Added `@vercel/analytics` to dependencies

- **frontend/package-lock.json**
  - Updated with new dependency tree for @vercel/analytics

## Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router:
- The Analytics component is imported from `@vercel/analytics/next`
- It's placed inside the `<body>` tag of the root layout
- No additional configuration is required - analytics will start collecting data once deployed to Vercel

## Verification Steps Completed

✓ TypeScript compilation: No errors
✓ Next.js build: Successful (all 29 routes built successfully)
✓ ESLint: No linting errors
✓ All existing functionality preserved

## Next Steps

When deployed to Vercel:
1. The Analytics component will automatically start collecting page view data
2. Vercel will add routes scoped at `/_vercel/insights/*` for analytics
3. Data will be visible in the Vercel dashboard under the Analytics section
4. Browser network tab will show requests to `/<unique-path>/view` once deployed

No further configuration is required. The analytics will work automatically once the app is deployed to Vercel.
